      <title>Parallel Combinator</title>
	  <xi:include
         href="&ug;"
         xpointer="&fx;combinators.parallel&xf;"
      />
      <frag id="ref.combinators.parallel.syntax">
		  <para>EBNF: E ::= ... | . E | E </para>
		  <para>Precedence: parallel > pruning > otherwise</para>
		  <para>Associativity: left and right </para>
		  <para>Commutative: true </para>
	  </frag>
	  <frag id="ref.combinators.parallel.behavior">
		  <para>
			  Orc executes the expression F | G by executing F and G concurrently. 
			  Whenever F or G communicates with a service or publishes a value, F | G does so as well. 
			  The resulting publications of F | G may be published in arbitrary order. 
		  </para>
	  </frag>
